<collectingCountry box="[359,443,585,611]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="579">INDIA</collectingCountry>
: Andaman Islands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="579" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,720]" pageId="3" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,621,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="579">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is recorded only from the Andaman Islands (
<collectingCountry box="[975,1038,621,648]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="579">India</collectingCountry>
), which are distant from the Indian mainland. It is different from all other Indian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" box="[680,795,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Brachinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[680,795,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="579">Brachinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the presence of two reddish yellow spots on frons (head).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
